                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17613857" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Fri, 7 Oct 2022 04:20:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think that should be a problem. However, it is a bigger problem to me that the code expects it to be a DefaultLogBuilder. We really should be using ServiceLoader to find a factory to create the LogBuilder implementation so users can provide their own if needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17616045" author="pkarwasz" created="Tue, 11 Oct 2022 19:13:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DefaultLogBuilder&lt;/tt&gt; is basically a &lt;tt&gt;LogBuilder&lt;/tt&gt; with an integrated &lt;tt&gt;reset()&lt;/tt&gt; method. As is we can not get rid of it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However if we were to move the &lt;a href=&quot;https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/log4j-layout-template-json/apidocs/org/apache/logging/log4j/layout/template/json/util/Recycler.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Recycler&lt;/a&gt; interface to the API, we could replace the &lt;tt&gt;ThreadLocal&amp;lt;DefaultLogBuilder&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; with &lt;tt&gt;Recycler&amp;lt;LogBuilder&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17616189" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Wed, 12 Oct 2022 05:20:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think you might be missing the point. I don&apos;t mind DefaultLogBuilder. I do mind that it is hard-coded to use it. Users should be able to provide their own implementation and right now they cannot.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
